fees.description: Dishonoured Payment fee of $9.50 (inc GST) may apply to payments we attempt that are subsequently declined.
A $19.00 (inc GST) fee may apply each time you request to move into a property.
A $19.00 (inc GST) fee may apply each time you request to move out of a property.
A $50.15 (inc GST) fee may apply each time you request a reconnection after disconnection for non-payment.

electricityContract.terms: See our Standing terms and conditions at www.dodo.com/energy/terms-prices-and-regulatory-information. If you are eligible, you can apply to receive QLD Government rebates when you sign up with us.
electricityContract.variation: We may vary these prices no more than once every 6 months, and provide you notice of any changes at least 10 business days before the change is effective. We will publish variations on our website and in a newspaper at least 10 business days prior.

singleRate.description: Supply will be available for a minimum 8 hours per day, at the discretion of the distributor, generally between 10pm and 7am.
Supply will be available for a minimum 18 hours per day, at the absolute discretion of the distributor.

solarFeedInTariff.description: Retailer Feed-in Tariff - This plan is available to eligible small solar customers with a maximum 10kW panel size and an inverter system no greater than 10kW as part of an ongoing contract.

electricityContract.onExpiryDescription: Standing contracts do not expire until you notify us in accordance with our Standing Contract Terms and Conditions.
electricityContract.additionalFeeInformation: For further details on the information and fees presented, or the terms and conditions of the contract, please visit www.dodo.com/energy/terms-prices-and-regulatory-information or contact us on 13 dodo (13 36 36).
